<reference id="u" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>u</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>u</xmlelement> element is typically used to apply underline highlighting
to the content of the element. <ph
conref="../../common/conref-file.dita#reuse_file/highlight-caution"/> For example, for specific
items such as GUI controls, use the <xmlelement>uicontrol</xmlelement> element.</shortdesc>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm>u</indexterm><indexterm>highlighting domain<indexterm>u</indexterm></indexterm>
</keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section id="section-1">
<note >Style sheets can be used to format the <xmlelement>u</xmlelement>
element differently, just like any other element can be restyled. Thus, it is not the case that
content in <xmlelement>u</xmlelement> elements will necessarily be rendered as underlined.</note>
</section>
